# FastAPI backend conventions

## General

Use FastAPI with:
- Pydantic models for request and response contracts
- service modules for business logic
- explicit typed return shapes
- small focused files

## Preferred layout

- app/api/
- app/models/
- app/schemas/
- app/services/
- app/db/
- app/core/

## Service boundaries

Keep separate services for:
- scan_service
- render_service
- extraction_service
- page_type_service
- scoring_service
- llm_service
- report_service

## API design

Routes should be explicit and REST-like.

Main routes:
- POST /api/scans
- GET /api/scans/{scan_id}
- POST /api/scans/{scan_id}/rescan
- PATCH /api/scans/{scan_id}/page-type
- POST /api/scans/{scan_id}/public-report
- GET /api/public-reports/{public_id}

## Error handling

Return explicit error states and error codes.
Do not hide partial failures.
Persist limitations and confidence impact.

## Scoring integration

Backend should never hardcode final copy inside route handlers.
Route handlers should orchestrate services, not implement scoring logic inline.

## Persistence

Persist:
- scan status
- fetch/render info
- extraction object
- scores
- issues
- recommendations
- llm output metadata